        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 3:59PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Poages Mill, or near Salem, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail. Heavy Rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Vinton...
Troutville...
New Castle...
Catawba...
and Hollins.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
